<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1039,1676]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1580,1605]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is placed in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1871" box="[651,800,1580,1604]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Agama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melicausa">
<emphasis box="[651,800,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">O. melicausa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group and is likely sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schuster, 1958" authorityName="Schuster" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Odontophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="territa">
<emphasis box="[1218,1324,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">O. territa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schuster" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" refString="Schuster, R. M. (1958) A revision of the sphaeropthalmine Mutillidae of America north of Mexico. II. Entomologica Americana, 37, 1 - 130." type="journal article" year="1958">Schuster, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Pitts 
<emphasis box="[283,341,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">et al.</emphasis>
2009). This species is most abundant in the Sonoran Desert (e.g. Wilson 
<emphasis box="[1182,1240,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">et al.</emphasis>
2010; Pitts 
<emphasis box="[1378,1436,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">et al.</emphasis>
2009, 2010a).
</paragraph>
